---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import MedicalDisclaimer from '../../components/MedicalDisclaimer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Caregiver Support"
  description="Resources and guidance for caregivers of mantle cell lymphoma patients — practical tips, emotional support, and self-care strategies."
>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-primary/5 via-warm-white to-sage/20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-charcoal mb-6">Caregiver Support</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-charcoal/60 leading-relaxed">
        Caring for someone with MCL is a journey. Here's how to support your loved one — and yourself.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-warm-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose max-w-none">
        <p class="text-lg text-charcoal/70 leading-relaxed">
          As a caregiver to someone with MCL, you play an essential role in their care and wellbeing. But caregiving can be demanding — physically, emotionally, and practically. You deserve support too.
        </p>

        <h2>Your Role as a Caregiver</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal/70">
          Caregivers often take on many roles: advocate, organizer, emotional support, researcher, and more. Common responsibilities include:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-charcoal/70 space-y-2">
          <li>Attending medical appointments and helping track treatment plans</li>
          <li>Managing medications and side effects</li>
          <li>Coordinating with the care team and insurance</li>
          <li>Providing emotional support and companionship</li>
          <li>Managing household responsibilities</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Practical Tips</h2>
        <ul class="text-charcoal/70 space-y-3">
          <li><strong>Stay organized:</strong> Keep a binder or digital folder with medical records, test results, medication lists, and appointment schedules.</li>
          <li><strong>Take notes:</strong> Bring a notebook to appointments and write down key information. Don't hesitate to ask the care team to repeat or clarify.</li>
          <li><strong>Accept help:</strong> When friends and family offer support, let them help with meals, errands, or companionship.</li>
          <li><strong>Communicate with the care team:</strong> Don't be afraid to ask questions or raise concerns. You know your loved one best.</li>
          <li><strong>Plan ahead:</strong> Talk with your loved one about preferences, advance directives, and financial planning when they feel well enough for those conversations.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Taking Care of Yourself</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal/70">
          Caregiver burnout is real and common. Prioritizing your own health isn't selfish — it's necessary.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-charcoal/70 space-y-3">
          <li><strong>Maintain your health:</strong> Keep up with your own medical appointments, exercise, and sleep.</li>
          <li><strong>Seek emotional support:</strong> Talk to friends, family, a therapist, or a caregiver support group. Processing your feelings is important.</li>
          <li><strong>Take breaks:</strong> Even short breaks can help you recharge. Ask someone to step in so you can have time for yourself.</li>
          <li><strong>Set boundaries:</strong> It's okay to say no or to delegate. You cannot do everything.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Caregiver Resources</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 not-prose my-8">
          <div class="bg-sage/30 rounded-xl p-5">
            <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Support Groups</h3>
            <p class="text-charcoal/60 text-sm">Connect with other MCL caregivers who understand your experience.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-sage/30 rounded-xl p-5">
            <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Financial Assistance</h3>
            <p class="text-charcoal/60 text-sm">Programs that can help with treatment costs, transportation, and other expenses.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-sage/30 rounded-xl p-5">
            <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Mental Health</h3>
            <p class="text-charcoal/60 text-sm">Counseling and therapy resources for caregivers managing stress and anxiety.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-sage/30 rounded-xl p-5">
            <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Respite Care</h3>
            <p class="text-charcoal/60 text-sm">Temporary relief services so caregivers can take necessary breaks.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-sage/30 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-charcoal mb-3">We're Here for You</h3>
          <p class="text-charcoal/70 mb-4">
            MCLA is building resources specifically for caregivers. If you need support or have questions, please reach out.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-2.5 bg-teal-primary text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-teal-dark transition-colors no-underline text-sm"
          >
            Contact Us
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <MedicalDisclaimer />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
